@node Credits "Credits and Licence"

@{b}Credits@{ub}

Handy was written by Keith Wilkins in 1998-2007 for Windows.

Handy 0.80 for Windows was ported to AmigaOS 4.0 (and WarpUP) by Mathias
"AmiDog" Roslund in 2005.

Handy 0.90 for Windows and Handy 0.80 for OS4 were merged and improved in
January 2007 by James Jacobs of Amigan Software to create Handy 0.90 for
OS3.0. When Handy 0.95 for Windows was released in February 2007, the core
of Handy 0.90 for OS3.0 was updated to create Handy 0.95 for OS3.0.

Handy 0.95 for Amiga 68K R1.02 was ported by Ilkka Lehtoranta in 2007 to
MorphOS and improved to create Handy++ (Handy 0.95 for MorphOS).

Special thanks to AmiDog for providing his source code to allow this
version to be created, and to Stefan Haubenthal for bug reports.

